		<title>11Modern Ormskirk Farming</title>
		<content>                                       
                                       
   One of the largest farms has 14     
tractors, one digger and one bulldozer 
and employs 17 people, rising to 30 in 
summer.    No working horses are used  
in the area.                           
   We were lucky to see a helicopter   
spraying fungicide over the crops when 
we were surveying our area.  However,  
the land is still drained by ditches   
and flashes (small ponds with sloping  
sides) as it has been for centuries.   
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
